@flexiarg coordination/capability-gate
@title Capability Gate (G4)
@keywords auth, capability, registry, assignment, reject
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/error-hierarchy futon-theory/stop-the-line]
@theory-grounding [A2(Attributable) A4(Degradation-detectable)]

! conclusion:
  If you want reliable coordination, gate task execution on an explicit capability match between the task requirements and the registered agent.

  + context: "Agent can do it" must be checked, not assumed.
  + IF:
    you want to route tasks to heterogeneous agents (humans, Codex, Claude, services)

  + HOWEVER:
    without authorization, tasks can be executed by agents that lack tools, permissions, or responsibility

  + THEN:
    require the agent to be present in the registry and validate capability match at G4

  + BECAUSE:
    otherwise failures are silent and attribution is unclear (who was supposed to do what?)

